The paper proposes a novel graph pooling operator for graph neural networks, which is a popular topic in machine learning research. The paper focuses on graph classification tasks, which are commonly studied in the subfield of deep learning known as graph representation learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves structure learning, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) research. The paper also mentions using the proposed method for natural language processing tasks (cs.CL), which often involve graph-based representations. Finally, the paper uses neural networks, which are a common tool in the subfield of neural engineering (cs.NE).
